{
  "texts": [
    "However, different from ICAE, 500xCompressor feeds the decoder with the KV pairs of the compression tokens rather than the continous vectors themselves.",
    "These KV pairs keep more detailed information than embedding vectors, especially under high compression ratios.",
    "500xCompressor uses a small number of tokens (1-16) to compress longer sequences (up to 480 tokens), achieving compression ratios from 6x to 480x, while retaining more than 60-70% of the capabilities of the uncompressed prompts.",
    "Moreover, the test set ArxivQA, generated from arXiv abstracts from January to April 2024, ensures evaluation on strictly unseen data, mitigating potential data leakage.",
    "Though 500xCompressor collects the KV pairs for the compression tokens, it does not modify them, thus 500xCompressor is a prompt compression method not a KV compression method."
  ]
}